Package: krill-pi4j
Version: 0.0.2
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: i2c-tools
Suggests: pigpiod
Maintainer: Benjamin Sautner <ben@krill.zone>
Description: Krill Pi4J gRPC Service for Raspberry Pi
 Exposes the pi4j-ktx hardware abstraction layer (GPIO, PWM, I2C) as a
 local gRPC service on port 50051.  Clients running on any JDK version
 can use the generated stubs to control hardware without needing JDK 25.
 .
 This package is a companion to the Krill Server (krill) and is intended
 to be installed alongside it on Raspberry Pi hardware. Learn more at https://krillswarm.com
 .
 Requires Java 25 or later (Zulu 25 recommended on ARM64).
